    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-13T04:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-13T04:43:00-05:00" n="688"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5833</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-13T09:00:00-00:43">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1917, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.42 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday Liberian Government received the following cablegram: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>British and French Governments advise declaration of war. Will guarantee
                            protection. Trade restrictions will be removed. Crommelin.<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d688fn2">Liberian Minister in Great Britain.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Liberian Government awaits the advice of the Government of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
